.TH SECONDS 3RPG  2010-03-10 "ILE RPG Language Reference"
.SH NAME
%SECONDS - Number of Seconds
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
%SECONDS(number)
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fB%SECONDS\fR converts a number into a duration that can be added to a time or timestamp value\[char46]





\fB%SECONDS\fR can only be the right-hand value in an addition or subtraction operation\[char46] The left-hand value must be a time or timestamp\[char46] The result is a time or timestamp value with the appropriate number of seconds added or subtracted\[char46] For a time, the resulting value is in \fI*ISO\fR format\[char46]


For an example of date and time arithmetic operations, see Figure 232\[char46]


For more information, see Date Operations or Built-in Functions\[char46]



















